12/06/2007
THE Hague, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal on Tuesday (June 12th) sentenced former Croatian Serb leader Milan Martic to 35 years in prison for the murder, torture and persecution of non-Serbs in Croatia. 
The former president of the breakaway state of Srpska Krajina was also found guilty of ordering two days of indiscriminate cluster bomb shelling of Zagreb in May 1995, causing seven deaths and hundreds of injuries. 
Martic was acquitted, however, of extermination. 
(RTRS, AP, Reuters - 12/06/07)
